You: "An iconic duo I take it?"

Shivers: Under the night sky the great district sleeps: A black chessboard of old wooden houses, 80,000 living souls inside. Firetraps as far as the eye can see -- from Main Street to Precinct 41 atop the motorway, to Boogie Street forking into the darkened horizon...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Detective, we just stopped a small-scale war. Something is happening to Revachol." He takes a look around -- into the deepening shadows of the streets -- then pulls up his collar.
Kim Kitsuragi: "No -- good luck with *your* report." The lieutenant smiles warmly.
Esprit de Corps: Detective Kuuno de Ruyter.
You: "Yeah... no. You're staying here, Cuno. You're too young."
Cuno: "THE FUCK?!" He spreads his arms. "Cuno's been *seen* with you, out in the open. He's free game right now. Singin' to the popophone. Fuckin' informant shit. Got pig all over me -- smoked pig."
Jean Vicquemare: "He meant *join* us. At Precinct 41. Transfer."

Jean Vicquemare: "He can't be a cop, Harry. He's a child. A child who says 'f****t' every four seconds."

You: "I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For the white banner of the Commune."

"I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For myself. For *my* life."
"I know it's difficult to believe, but I will do it. For the RCM."

Jean Vicquemare: "Well -- now you're a cop," he pauses, "or... not anymore, so I guess you're a gym teacher again."
